prompt: You change your privacy settings on a social networking site to share posts with your friends only. Should you feel safe sharing an embarrassing personal photo with this setting, if you would be horrified if anyone but a friend ever saw it?
feedback: Privacy settings can be important and help keep your information from becoming public, but it’s easy for information to get copied and moved on the Internet. If you’re very concerned about a photo or any other information, it’s safer not to share it than to rely on privacy settings. Even if your post is only shared with friends, your friends could re-share your post.
